{
  "Question": "<p>The math book i'm using states that the cross product for two vectors is defined over <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_56\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"R^{3}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>R</mi> <mn>3</mn> </msup> </math></span>:</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_57\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"u=(a,b,c)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>u</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>a</mi> <mo>,</mo> <mi>b</mi> <mo>,</mo> <mi>c</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span><br/> <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_58\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"v=(d,e,f)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>v</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>d</mi> <mo>,</mo> <mi>e</mi> <mo>,</mo> <mi>f</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>is:</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_59\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"u\\times v=\\vmatrix\\hat{i}&amp;amp;\\hat{j}&amp;amp;\\hat{k}\\\\\na&amp;amp;b&amp;amp;c\\\\\nd&amp;amp;e&amp;amp;f\\\\\n\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>u</mi> <mo>\u00d7</mo> <mi>v</mi> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>{vmatrix}</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mover accent=\"true\"> <mi>i</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">^</mo> </mover> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>a</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>m</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>p</mi> </mrow> <mo>;</mo> <mrow> <mover accent=\"true\"> <mi>j</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">^</mo> </mover> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>a</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>m</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>p</mi> </mrow> <mo>;</mo> <mrow> <mover accent=\"true\"> <mi>k</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">^</mo> </mover> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>a</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>a</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>m</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>p</mi> </mrow> <mo>;</mo> <mrow> <mi>b</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>a</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>m</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>p</mi> </mrow> <mo>;</mo> <mrow> <mi>c</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>d</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>a</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>m</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>p</mi> </mrow> <mo>;</mo> <mrow> <mi>e</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>a</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>m</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>p</mi> </mrow> <mo>;</mo> <mi>f</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>and the direction of the resultant is determined by curling fingers from vector v to u with thumb pointing in direction of the cross product of u x v.</p> <hr/> <p>Out of curiosity, what's the cross product if u and v are defined over <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_60\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"R^{2}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>R</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </math></span> instead of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_61\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"R^{3}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>R</mi> <mn>3</mn> </msup> </math></span> instead:</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_62\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"u=(a,b)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>u</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>a</mi> <mo>,</mo> <mi>b</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span><br/> <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_63\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"v=(d,e)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>v</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>d</mi> <mo>,</mo> <mi>e</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>Is there a \"degenerate\" case for the cross product of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_64\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"R^{2}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>R</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </math></span> instead <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_65\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"R^{3}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>R</mi> <mn>3</mn> </msup> </math></span>?  like this is some type of 2x2 determinant instead?</p> <p>for instance if had a parameterization:</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_66\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\Phi(u,\\ v)=(\\ f(u),\\ \\ g(v)\\ )\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03a6</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>u</mi> <mo rspace=\"7.5pt\">,</mo> <mi>v</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mo rspace=\"7.5pt\" stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mi>f</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>u</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo rspace=\"12.5pt\">,</mo> <mrow> <mi>g</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>v</mi> <mo rspace=\"7.5pt\" stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>and needed to calculate in <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_67\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"R^{2}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>R</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </math></span>:</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_68\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"D=\\Bigg{|}\\frac{\\partial{\\Phi}}{\\partial{u}}\\times\\frac{\\partial{\\Phi}}{%\n\\partial{v}}\\Bigg{|}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>D</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mo maxsize=\"260%\" minsize=\"260%\">|</mo> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mo>\u2202</mo> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03a6</mi> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>\u2202</mo> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mi>u</mi> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>\u00d7</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mo>\u2202</mo> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03a6</mi> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>\u2202</mo> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mi>v</mi> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo maxsize=\"260%\" minsize=\"260%\">|</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>There are plenty of examples in the book for calculating the determinate D in <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_69\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"R^{3}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>R</mi> <mn>3</mn> </msup> </math></span> but none at all for <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_70\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"R^{2}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>R</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </math></span> case.</p> <p>As in:</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_71\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\iint_{V}f(x,y)dx\\ dy=\\iint_{Q}f(\\Phi(u,v)\\Bigg{|}\\frac{\\partial{\\Phi}}{%\n\\partial{u}}\\times\\frac{\\partial{\\Phi}}{\\partial{v}}\\Bigg{|}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msub> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\iint</mtext> </merror> <mi>V</mi> </msub> <mi>f</mi> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>,</mo> <mi>y</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mi>d</mi> <mpadded width=\"+5pt\"> <mi>x</mi> </mpadded> <mi>d</mi> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <msub> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\iint</mtext> </merror> <mi>Q</mi> </msub> <mi>f</mi> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03a6</mi> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>u</mi> <mo>,</mo> <mi>v</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mo maxsize=\"260%\" minsize=\"260%\">|</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mo>\u2202</mo> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03a6</mi> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>\u2202</mo> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mi>u</mi> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>\u00d7</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mo>\u2202</mo> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03a6</mi> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>\u2202</mo> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mi>v</mi> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo maxsize=\"260%\" minsize=\"260%\">|</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_72\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\Phi(u,v)=(2u\\cos v,\\ \\ u\\sin v)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03a6</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>u</mi> <mo>,</mo> <mi>v</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>u</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mi>cos</mi> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mi>v</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo rspace=\"12.5pt\">,</mo> <mrow> <mi>u</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mi>sin</mi> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mi>v</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p>",
  "Title": "What's the cross product in 2 dimensions?",
